info.name: Butter Chicken
info.category: North Indain Non Veg Main Course
info.description: Chicken with bone is first baked in the tandoor and later cooked in a gravy with butter, tomatoes, kasoori methi and kashmiri chillies and finished off with more melted butter

info.name: Chicken Kholapuri
info.category: North Indain Non Veg Main Course
info.description: Chicken pieces with bone are cooked in a kohlapuri masala from the kohlapur region of maharashtra containing whole coriander, stone flower, white sesame among others and topped with fresh coriander.

info.name: Kadai Chicken
info.category: North Indain Non Veg Main Course
info.description: Chicken with bone cooked with initially with garlic, ginger and green chillies and then diced onions and tomatoes are added in with classic indian spices and slow cooked.

info.name: Prawns Fry
info.description: Fresh medium size prawns marinated in chilli powder, fresh pepper and spices and deep fried to crispiness.

info.name: Eripori Chicken
info.description: Boneless chicken pieces are fried in coconut oil with masala, madras onions and curry leaves and then mixed with jeera  and crushed red chillies and stir fried to a crispy finish.

info.name: Chicken Kothi Thaalichath
info.description: Shredded chicken pieces in kerala masala is cooked with ginger, garlic, sliced coconut and curry leave and slow sauted with pepper and coconut till done.

info.name: Mutton Pepper Fry
info.description: The aroma of kerala’s crushed black pepper in the august company of coconut oil, spices and curry leaves gives this mutton dish the meat flavor in a delicious combination of slow frying with kerala spices.

info.name: Chicken Kondattam
info.description: Boneless chicken pieces are cooked in traditionally curd dipped and sundried chillies, coriander and curry leaves for a spicy, dry, chicken starter dish.

info.name: Onion Pakoda
info.description: Deep fried onions mixed with besan flour for a crispy tea time snack with tea/coffee.

info.name: Chilly Chicken
info.description: The sweet and spicy indian chinese favourite.  Chicken is stir fried with chilli and soy sauce along with bell peppers and garlic.

info.name: Sear Fish Nirvana
info.description: Chef pillai evolved the meen pollichathu, a fish delicacy into his own signature dish aptly named nirvana. Fresh slices of seer fish is pan fried with a marinated masala and then gently placed in a banana leaf which rests on a hopper pan or appam chatti. The coconut milk is gently poured into it and allowed to be cooked. This ensures that the fish is juicy, the masalas being blended with the coconut milk, ginger, curry leaves & green chilies.

info.name: Tawa Fried Sear Fish
info.description: The traditional way of frying fish in kerala. The fish are first marinated with spices such as chilli, pepper and turmeric powder and gently tawa fried to retain the suppleness.
